'''摩摩喳喳'''（'''Burburchacha'''、'''bobochacha'''或'''momochacha'''），是來自[[馬來西亞|馬來西亞]]及[[新加坡|新加坡]]的[[甜湯|甜湯]]，可以做冰品，也可以溫熱時食用，有點類似中國的[[八寶粥|八寶粥]]，是馬來西亞、[[泰國|泰國]]、新加坡、[[越南|越南]]等東南亞國家代表性食物<ref>[http://www.hb.xinhuanet.com/2015-03/16/c_1114651020.htm 武汉万达嘉华酒店泰国美食节4月即将启幕] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150414160045/http://www.hb.xinhuanet.com/2015-03/16/c_1114651020.htm |date=2015-04-14 }}</ref>。主要原料有[[椰奶|椰奶]]、[[水椰|亞答籽]]、[[西米露|西米露]]等，<ref> {{Cite book | author = Tan Chee-Beng | title = Chinese food and foodways in Southeast Asia and beyond | url = https://archive.org/details/chinesefoodfoodw0000zhon | location = Singapore | publisher = NUS Press | date = 2011 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/chinesefoodfoodw0000zhon/page/36 36]-7 | ISBN = 978-9971-69-548-4 | accessdate = 2015-04-02 | language = En | quote = Burbur Chacha (this is a desert containing medley of sweet potato, taro, sago, and others in coconut milk etc.)}} </ref> 也會加入[[芋頭|芋頭]]丁、[[番薯|地瓜]]丁，及像[[紅毛丹|紅毛丹]]、[[蘭撒|龍宮果]]、[[菠蘿蜜|菠蘿蜜]]等南洋水果。此甜點在港澳稱[[咋喳|咋喳]](Cha Cha)，配料以豆類為主<ref> {{Cite book | author = Tan Chee-Beng | title = Chinese food and foodways in Southeast Asia and beyond | url = https://archive.org/details/chinesefoodfoodw0000zhon | location = Singapore | publisher = NUS Press | date = 2011 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/chinesefoodfoodw0000zhon/page/44 44] | ISBN = 978-9971-69-548-4 | accessdate = 2015-04-02 | language = En | quote = This dish is known as Cha Cha in Hong Kong, and the ingredients differ somewhat, with more use of beans than sweet potato and taro.}} </ref>，近來亦有添加芋頭或地瓜的咋喳。

